==Variants==
===SLASH’EM===
In [[SLASH'EM]], two rolling boulder traps appear in set locations within the [[Lawful Quest]].

===UnNetHack===
In [[UnNetHack]], 10% of rolling boulder traps will also generate an [[archaeologist]] corpse, a [[bullwhip]], and a [[fedora]] with a {{frac|3}} chance.

===xNetHack===
In [[xNetHack]], the player does not trigger rolling boulder traps unless actually standing on the ground, as with monsters triggering the trap. Rolling boulder traps also have a chance of generating an archaeologist corpse, a bullwhip, and a fedora with a {{frac|3}} chance.

